      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adult patients undergoing elective surgery.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Difficult peripheral venous access

          -  Allergy to gelatin

          -  Symptomatic cardiac disease, rhythm trouble, pace-maker, aortic valvular disease,
             aortic disease

          -  Morbid obesity, low BMI,

          -  hypovolemia,

          -  Raynaud syndrome or scleroderma,

          -  Contra-indication to propofol, remifentanil or to the use of Bispectral Index,

          -  Hematocrit &lt; 20%.
      </textblock>
